page.title: 09THE MOAT HOUSE GRT.C.
page.content: Parts of the house are 400 years old. The Moat round the house is mentioned in the ancient Domesday Book. There are 4 protected trees in the house grounds. One of the trees is called Wellingtonia it is over 160 years old. The Wellingtonia is planted to remember the Duke of Wellington. The Oregon Pine is one hundred and fifty years old. The Turkey oak is one hundred and forty years old, the other protected tree we think is a Walnut tree. The Turkey Oak's trunk measured three metres eighty-two cm. The Wellingtonia's trunk measured four metres thirty cm. The Walnut tree's trunk measured two metres sixty-three cm.
